Chromosome number
:—2n = 32 (
Ma & Gilbert 2008
); n = 8 (
Trivedi & Trivedi 1992
); 2n = 16 (
Krishnappa & Reshme 1980
); 2n = 28 (
Hans 1973
); n = 14, 28 (
Hans 1973
); 2n = 56 (Gill 
et al.
1970).

Ecology :—Accidentally dispersed by humans as contaminant; globally considered as weed of orchards and plantations. Typical of open and disturbed areas (
Steinmann et al. 2016
), it also colonizes flowerbeds and roadsides.
